  "prompt": "Is there a way to sync music to iPhone without iTunes?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several ways to sync music to your iPhone without using iTunes. Here are a few methods:\n\n1. **Apple Music or iCloud Music Library**: If you have an Apple Music subscription or use iCloud Music Library, you can upload your music to the cloud and access it from your iPhone. Just make sure that both your computer and iPhone are signed in with the same Apple ID and have iCloud Music Library enabled.\n\n2. **Third-Party Apps**: There are various third-party apps and software that allow music transfer, such as:\n   - **WALTR**: This app lets you drag and drop music files to your iPhone wirelessly or via USB.\n   - **iMazing**: A comprehensive iOS device manager that enables music transfer among other things.\n   - **MediaMonkey**: A media manager that can sync with iOS devices.\n\n3. **Cloud Storage Services**: You can use services like Dropbox, Google Drive, or OneDrive. Upload your music files to the cloud service and then use the respective app on your iPhone to access and download the files.\n\n4. **Music Streaming Services**: If you're using services like Spotify, Amazon Music, or Google Play Music, you can upload your music to their cloud service and listen to it on your iPhone through their app.\n\n5. **File Sharing Apps**: Apps like SHAREit or Airdrop (for Mac users) can wirelessly transfer music files directly from your computer to your iPhone.\n\nBefore using a third-party solution, ensure it is trustworthy to keep your data safe.",
